			<ns0:name>robe...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/108771824208521698652/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Broadening the bug to a general simplification and cleanup of file extensions use by the driver. 
This should ultimately simplify the driver and make its behavior less magical.

Current plan:
.bc =&gt; bitcode   (this will be tricky for (new)libc and libstdc++)
.o  =&gt; true object files   
.pexe =&gt; giant pre-linked bitcode file

it would also be nice to have separate  extension for object and bitcode libraries instead of using .a for both</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2011-03-11T15:07:44.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2011-03-11T15:07:44.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:updates /><ns0:title>Comment 3 by robe...@google.com</ns0:title><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=1514#c3" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><ns0:link href="https://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/1514/comments/full/3" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /></ns0:entry>